WEBVTT

00:02.045 --> 00:05.005
["Zoom" by Freedom Fly playing]

00:05.048 --> 00:07.442
♪ Ah... ♪

00:10.575 --> 00:12.838
NANCY: Any other day, an evil sea spirit

00:12.882 --> 00:14.623
wants to send me
a foreboding omen,

00:14.666 --> 00:16.059
I'm game.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.234
Just not the day of my dad's

00:17.278 --> 00:18.844
evidentiary hearing.

00:18.888 --> 00:21.369
♪ In the heat of the moment ♪

00:21.412 --> 00:25.068
♪ The heat of the moment ♪

00:25.112 --> 00:27.027
♪ We can change it all ♪

00:27.070 --> 00:29.333
♪ Breaking down the walls... ♪

00:29.377 --> 00:32.554
Thanks for letting me crash
on your couch last night.

00:32.597 --> 00:34.469
Oh, I slept like a log.

00:34.512 --> 00:35.905
Sure about that?

00:35.948 --> 00:39.169
Come on in, John,
welcome to The Claw.

00:39.213 --> 00:42.172
Wow, it's much bigger
than it looks on FaceTime.

00:42.216 --> 00:43.347
Hey!

00:43.391 --> 00:44.827
So are you.

00:44.870 --> 00:46.481
Thank you for coming
all this way.

00:46.524 --> 00:49.092
Well, it beats sneaking illegal
human bones into my lab.

00:49.136 --> 00:51.138
But I'd do anything for Nancy.

00:51.181 --> 00:52.661
Where is she?
She's here.

00:52.704 --> 00:53.923
[FaceTime ringing]

00:53.966 --> 00:55.272
NANCY:
Hey, John.

00:55.316 --> 00:56.621
I'll be there as soon as I can.

00:56.665 --> 00:58.928
I'm just waiting
on Lucy's case files.

00:58.971 --> 01:02.627
My dad's lawyer is sending me a
copy ahead of his hearing today.

01:02.671 --> 01:05.065
The prosecution wants me
to testify at 3:00 p.m.

01:05.108 --> 01:08.633
So I have until then to find
the hard proof to exonerate him.

01:08.677 --> 01:10.331
That's where the bones come in.

01:10.374 --> 01:11.419
Yeah.

01:11.462 --> 01:13.247
They may not be admissible...

01:13.290 --> 01:15.292
in the court, but...

01:15.336 --> 01:16.902
if they tell us something
about the killer,

01:16.946 --> 01:18.730
then maybe I can track
that evidence down.

01:18.774 --> 01:20.080
JOHN:
Now, what makes you think

01:20.123 --> 01:21.429
the remains of a girl who died

01:21.472 --> 01:23.996
20 years ago suddenly
just appeared?

01:24.040 --> 01:25.215
♪ Take another go ♪

01:25.259 --> 01:27.522
♪ Next thing you know... ♪

01:27.565 --> 01:30.264
We performed a mystical ritual

01:30.307 --> 01:33.223
asking an evil spirit for them.

01:33.267 --> 01:35.312
Got it.

01:35.356 --> 01:36.487
You don't want to tell me.

01:36.531 --> 01:37.749
I probably don't want to know.

01:37.793 --> 01:38.750
[doorbell rings]

01:38.794 --> 01:40.012
Oh, that's the Lucy files.

01:40.056 --> 01:41.492
They should have
her dental records,

01:41.536 --> 01:43.451
so you can confirm
the identity of the bones.

01:43.494 --> 01:45.844
I'll be by in a bit.

01:45.888 --> 01:48.325
I assume you kept these bones in
a sanitary, sterile environment,

01:48.369 --> 01:50.762
as per basic
scientific guidelines?

01:50.806 --> 01:52.286
♪ Ooh ♪

01:56.116 --> 01:57.508
It's all I could find.

01:57.552 --> 02:00.816
Halloween box felt
a little on the nose.

02:00.859 --> 02:02.557
Let's just get to the lab,

02:02.600 --> 02:05.299
so we can start doing things
the right way.

02:05.342 --> 02:07.039
GEORGE:
Yeah...

02:07.083 --> 02:08.693
you're at the lab.
We're closed for the day.

02:08.737 --> 02:09.955
Place is yours.

02:09.999 --> 02:11.696
Well, round up your sanitizers.

02:11.740 --> 02:13.655
We got some scrubbing
ahead of us.

02:15.918 --> 02:17.354
Made that out of clay.

02:17.398 --> 02:20.009
Huh.

02:20.052 --> 02:22.142
[birds chirping outside]

02:22.185 --> 02:24.144
[indistinct chatter on TV]

02:31.455 --> 02:33.457
[sighs]

02:38.158 --> 02:40.377
CARSON:
I saw tire tracks in the dirt

02:40.421 --> 02:42.510
and Lucy's dress.

02:42.553 --> 02:44.468
NICK:
The Hudson shell company
made a sizeable,

02:44.512 --> 02:48.255
one-time payment
to your dad back in 2000.

02:48.298 --> 02:50.474
RYAN:
The same way they handled
everything back then...

02:50.518 --> 02:52.128
Carson Drew.

02:52.172 --> 02:53.825
NANCY:
Did you kill Lucy Sable?

02:53.869 --> 02:55.958
CARSON:
I didn't kill anyone!

02:56.001 --> 02:58.613
McGINNIS:
Your father's fingerprints
were on the knife.

02:58.656 --> 03:00.267
KAREN:
Carson Drew, you're under arrest

03:00.310 --> 03:02.269
for the murder of Lucy Sable.

03:02.312 --> 03:04.880
NANCY: He's been in jail for two
weeks and it's all my fault.

03:04.923 --> 03:06.751
CARSON:
After the evidentiary hearing tomorrow,

03:06.795 --> 03:08.405
they will most likely
transfer me

03:08.449 --> 03:10.712
to a prison in the next county.

03:11.800 --> 03:14.237
[sighs]

03:14.281 --> 03:16.283
A little help, Lucy?

03:17.545 --> 03:18.763
No?

03:18.807 --> 03:19.851
Nothing?

03:19.895 --> 03:22.767
No cryptic message?

03:22.811 --> 03:25.205
I am trying to solve your murder!

03:25.248 --> 03:28.164
[sighs]

03:58.803 --> 04:01.763
Okay, Lucy, what?

04:08.857 --> 04:10.685
The knife
from Lucy's crime scene.

04:22.000 --> 04:23.263
And the silver steak knives

04:23.306 --> 04:24.568
in the pantry.

04:24.612 --> 04:26.178
Yeah, yeah.

04:26.222 --> 04:28.137
The ones Mom loved so much?

04:28.180 --> 04:31.532
She always kept these
stored away in here.

04:34.012 --> 04:36.972
Lucy's crown had
a second set of DNA.

04:37.015 --> 04:38.278
Female DNA.

04:40.410 --> 04:42.543
NANCY: Did my mom have something to do

04:42.586 --> 04:44.936
with Lucy's death?

04:46.895 --> 04:49.419
♪ ♪

04:58.385 --> 05:00.343
[seagulls calling]

05:03.390 --> 05:04.956
Got Lucy's dental records.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.002
Did you find anything
else in the files?

05:07.045 --> 05:08.873
Not really.

05:08.917 --> 05:10.222
Hey, you know

05:10.266 --> 05:12.703
the other female hair
that was found

05:12.747 --> 05:15.184
on Lucy's crown... do you
still believe that that

05:15.227 --> 05:17.317
was from the last person
who saw her alive?

05:17.360 --> 05:18.970
I'd bet my license on it.

05:19.014 --> 05:20.363
Did you happen to sequence
that DNA, too?

05:20.407 --> 05:21.669
Of course,

05:21.712 --> 05:23.453
and I backed my data
up to the cloud

05:23.497 --> 05:25.107
before the physical
evidence went missing.

05:25.150 --> 05:26.761
I was hoping you would say that.

05:26.804 --> 05:28.676
I sent a lock of my hair
to your lab

05:28.719 --> 05:30.373
to compare with
the unknown hair to see

05:30.417 --> 05:32.636
if it's a mother-daughter
DNA match.

05:32.680 --> 05:34.943
Oh. Okay.

05:34.986 --> 05:36.553
I'll, uh, make a call

05:36.597 --> 05:39.469
and see if I can get
the results expedited.

05:39.513 --> 05:41.645
Wait, wait.

05:41.689 --> 05:44.518
You think your mum killed Lucy?

05:45.606 --> 05:47.390
If your dad's covering for her,

05:47.434 --> 05:49.131
that could explain some
of his cagey behavior.

05:49.174 --> 05:51.046
I'm just ruling out
any possibilities.

05:51.089 --> 05:54.397
She had no motive, so...

05:54.441 --> 05:56.356
The only thing that makes sense
is that Ryan killed Lucy,

05:56.399 --> 05:59.489
Everett found out, and then
called my dad in to clean it up.

05:59.533 --> 06:01.186
No, listen.

06:01.230 --> 06:02.753
You don't seem so sure.

06:02.797 --> 06:05.016
Okay, you know, maybe
you should rest.

06:05.060 --> 06:06.540
You got home late.

06:06.583 --> 06:08.542
Well... early.

06:08.585 --> 06:10.152
And you sounded pretty sick.

06:10.195 --> 06:11.414
Probably just stress.

06:11.458 --> 06:12.633
Maybe it's a bug.

06:12.676 --> 06:14.896
I tried to contact Owen today,

06:14.939 --> 06:16.376
but he didn't answer.

06:16.419 --> 06:17.638
He said that he was
gonna be out of town,

06:17.681 --> 06:19.030
so maybe he's got
the bug, too...

06:19.074 --> 06:20.641
Owen's fine.

06:20.684 --> 06:21.642
He's just tired.

06:21.685 --> 06:23.383
[gasps]

06:23.426 --> 06:24.993
You got in this morning,
and you know the reason

06:25.036 --> 06:27.735
why Owen is tired. Aah!

06:27.778 --> 06:29.650
You slept with my cousin!

06:33.262 --> 06:35.220
Nick, I'm really sorry.

06:35.264 --> 06:37.048
I didn't mean for you
to find out like that.

06:37.092 --> 06:39.007
No, it's fine.

06:39.050 --> 06:41.226
Bone time.

06:41.270 --> 06:44.229
It's pronounced
"forensic analysis."

06:44.273 --> 06:45.448
[clears throat]

06:45.492 --> 06:47.450
Okay, uh...

06:47.494 --> 06:49.017
so, if you guys are...

06:49.060 --> 06:51.106
if you guys are good here,
I'm just gonna, I'm gonna go

06:51.149 --> 06:54.022
and look over Ryan
and Lucy's e-mails.

06:54.065 --> 06:55.327
Divide and...

06:55.371 --> 06:57.808
divide and conquer.

06:57.852 --> 06:59.070
Sorry.

07:01.333 --> 07:03.423
Are you okay?

07:03.466 --> 07:05.468
That was...

07:05.512 --> 07:07.165
awkward.

07:08.645 --> 07:11.474
Yeah.

07:11.518 --> 07:12.997
I'm just...

07:13.041 --> 07:15.217
just surprised.

07:15.260 --> 07:16.566
Hmm.

07:16.610 --> 07:18.916
I guess the, uh...

07:18.960 --> 07:21.136
the grace period's over, huh?

07:21.179 --> 07:23.051
Yeah.

07:23.094 --> 07:25.053
But you know what?

07:25.096 --> 07:27.142
I'm-I'm... [chuckles]

07:27.185 --> 07:29.361
I'm actually really okay.

07:29.405 --> 07:31.886
Really?

07:31.929 --> 07:34.323
Yeah.

07:34.366 --> 07:35.846
[both laugh]

07:35.890 --> 07:39.023
Well... I'm glad.

07:39.067 --> 07:41.504
We should celebrate.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.811
Right, right.

07:43.854 --> 07:46.204
Like...

07:46.248 --> 07:49.033
maybe you don't have to sleep...

07:49.077 --> 07:51.645
on the couch tonight?

07:55.605 --> 07:57.259
Oh.
Be-Because it's...

07:57.302 --> 07:58.782
super uncomfortable.

07:58.826 --> 08:00.871
And...
I'd...

08:00.915 --> 08:03.134
I'd like to not sleep

08:03.178 --> 08:05.136
on the couch tonight.

08:05.180 --> 08:06.703
Okay.

08:06.747 --> 08:08.705
[siren chirps]

08:13.884 --> 08:15.756
The cops are here.

08:22.327 --> 08:23.415
Okay, okay.

08:23.459 --> 08:24.591
No one panic.

08:25.679 --> 08:27.550
[all clamoring]

08:27.594 --> 08:30.510
["Shame" by Sego playing]

08:36.603 --> 08:39.693
♪ Everyone's tryin' to sell me drugs ♪

08:39.736 --> 08:41.956
♪ I'm just like you, but lazy... ♪

08:41.999 --> 08:43.914
Can I help you?

08:43.958 --> 08:46.787
Detective Abe Tamura.

08:48.832 --> 08:51.443
Detective Abe...? Do you know this guy?

08:51.487 --> 08:53.576
I don't know... And this is the part
where you invite me in.

08:53.620 --> 08:55.578
Is he a vampire?

08:55.622 --> 08:56.623
Is he a...?

08:56.666 --> 08:57.841
Just open...
[bell jingles]

08:57.885 --> 09:00.975
Hey, come on in.

09:01.018 --> 09:02.019
Go.
NICK: Welcome.

09:02.063 --> 09:03.325
Welcome to The Claw.

09:03.368 --> 09:05.283
Uh, we-we're actually
closed today.

09:05.327 --> 09:07.198
What for?

09:07.242 --> 09:08.678
Private party.
Inventory.

09:08.722 --> 09:10.854
A little bit of both.

09:10.898 --> 09:13.596
[indistinct radio chatter]

09:13.640 --> 09:15.729
Hmm.

09:15.772 --> 09:17.078
Perfect.

09:17.121 --> 09:19.733
I have a warrant
to search the premises.

09:19.776 --> 09:21.517
And you have
no diners to disturb.

09:21.561 --> 09:22.866
Wait.

09:22.910 --> 09:24.346
Search this place?

09:24.389 --> 09:26.043
Really? Chief McGinnis brought me in

09:26.087 --> 09:27.958
to take over the Tiffany
Hudson investigation

09:28.002 --> 09:29.612
from the recently
discredited and,

09:29.656 --> 09:32.876
well, incarcerated Karen Hart.

09:35.052 --> 09:37.228
[siren chirps]

09:37.272 --> 09:39.361
We're surrounded.

09:39.404 --> 09:40.928
Don't be nervous.

09:40.971 --> 09:42.712
Unless you got a dead body

09:42.756 --> 09:44.584
hiding in one of these booths,
you got nothing to worry about.

09:44.627 --> 09:47.282
[both laughing]

09:47.325 --> 09:48.631
Kitchen's through here?

09:48.675 --> 09:50.198
Yeah.
Yeah, right through there.

09:50.241 --> 09:51.329
I'll show you.

09:51.373 --> 09:53.375
Just...
Come.

09:55.377 --> 09:57.379
The cooler.

10:05.126 --> 10:06.649
Right this way.
TAMURA: Take the booth by the window,

10:06.693 --> 10:08.085
where the husband was sitting.

10:08.129 --> 10:10.348
[indistinct chatter]

10:10.392 --> 10:11.741
What?

10:11.785 --> 10:13.482
That was a mess.

10:13.525 --> 10:16.137
We really need to get on the
same page about these things.

10:19.749 --> 10:22.578
[shushes]
[phone ringing]

10:22.622 --> 10:23.797
[grunts]

10:23.840 --> 10:25.929
Nancy, how are you doing?

10:25.973 --> 10:27.452
In Ryan's e-mails to Lucy,

10:27.496 --> 10:29.106
he used single spaces
after the periods.

10:29.150 --> 10:31.195
But in the last e-mail,

10:31.239 --> 10:33.676
where he called her a whore,
he uses double spaces.

10:33.720 --> 10:34.808
You think he didn't
write that one?

10:34.851 --> 10:36.070
Can you track the I.P. address

10:36.113 --> 10:37.680
to see, uh,
where it was sent from?

10:37.724 --> 10:39.421
Yeah. Yeah.

10:39.464 --> 10:41.292
Give me, uh, two minutes.

10:49.431 --> 10:50.998
NANCY:
Hey, Ryan.

10:51.041 --> 10:52.695
No, I just gave another
statement on my wife's murder.

10:52.739 --> 10:54.218
I'm really not in the mood.

10:54.262 --> 10:57.221
I know that you didn't
write that e-mail to Lucy.

10:57.265 --> 10:59.920
About hoping that she'd die.

11:04.751 --> 11:06.143
[quietly]:
Come here.

11:07.928 --> 11:10.539
It came from an I.P. address in Lisbon.

11:10.582 --> 11:13.629
Where, according to Forbes, your
dad was busy acquiring a company

11:13.673 --> 11:15.370
in 2000.

11:15.413 --> 11:18.678
Why would Everett impersonate
you in an e-mail to Lucy?

11:18.721 --> 11:20.070
I don't know.

11:20.114 --> 11:21.724
Okay, well, then,
let's find out.

11:21.768 --> 11:23.987
It is high time
that you tell me the whole truth

11:24.031 --> 11:26.033
about your relationship
with Lucy.

11:26.076 --> 11:28.165
Or I will turn those e-mails
over to the judge

11:28.209 --> 11:29.993
when I testify later today.

11:30.037 --> 11:32.561
I do not think
that you killed Lucy.

11:32.604 --> 11:34.084
But I do think

11:34.128 --> 11:37.174
that you are the key
to finding out who did.

11:37.218 --> 11:38.828
Please, Ryan.

11:42.919 --> 11:44.138
Okay.

11:45.182 --> 11:46.793
Okay.

11:58.326 --> 11:59.980
Well, I'll be.
This is Lucy Sable.
[shushes]

12:00.023 --> 12:01.764
[whispers]: The cops
are right outside the door.

12:01.808 --> 12:04.027
If we're to believe
Karen Hart's report,

12:04.071 --> 12:06.116
Joshua Dodd came in
through this back door,

12:06.160 --> 12:07.335
poisoned the victim's food
in there.

12:07.378 --> 12:09.816
[clattering]

12:11.774 --> 12:14.646
We'll start in the dining room.

12:24.221 --> 12:26.136
Now all we need
to do is stop them

12:26.180 --> 12:28.835
going into the cooler
in a non-suspicious way.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.880
Piece of cake.
GEORGE: Yeah. It would've been a lot cakier

12:30.924 --> 12:32.403
if you would let me handle it.

12:32.447 --> 12:34.405
Private party? Where are
the private partygoers?

12:34.449 --> 12:37.017
Oh, it is a far better deterrent
than "inventory."

12:37.060 --> 12:40.542
GEORGE:
Oh, yeah, says you.
Now I've got to slow them down.

12:40.585 --> 12:42.849
Who wants brunch? On the house.

12:44.415 --> 12:46.548
Hey. Except we can't get
to the food in the cooler.

12:46.591 --> 12:49.116
So then go grab sardines
and saltines from the back.

12:49.159 --> 12:50.378
What are you waiting for?

12:50.421 --> 12:52.119
[stammers]

12:52.162 --> 12:53.598
GEORGE:
Go.

12:53.642 --> 12:55.644
Oh, my God.

12:58.516 --> 13:00.867
What? He should have let me
handle it with the cops.

13:00.910 --> 13:03.608
Okay? We're co-bosses. We don't
have to "co" everything.

13:03.652 --> 13:04.827
Okay.

13:04.871 --> 13:06.829
What? Okay, listen,
if you've maxed out

13:06.873 --> 13:09.005
on "co's" before you've even
kissed each other,

13:09.049 --> 13:11.094
then maybe it's a sign

13:11.138 --> 13:13.227
you shouldn't be together.

13:14.881 --> 13:16.230
[whispers]:
Come on.

13:17.492 --> 13:19.015
[sighs]:
Okay.

13:19.059 --> 13:20.451
RYAN:
After the Velvet Masque,

13:20.495 --> 13:21.975
Lucy and I had to keep
our relationship

13:22.018 --> 13:23.411
a secret from my parents.

13:23.454 --> 13:25.587
Then your dad
found out in spring,

13:25.630 --> 13:28.590
and he made Lucy break up with
you and then he sent this e-mail

13:28.633 --> 13:31.027
to make sure
she stayed away for good.

13:31.071 --> 13:34.291
Why did you keep your
relationship with Lucy a secret,

13:34.335 --> 13:36.337
even after she died?

13:38.556 --> 13:40.167
I had to.

13:42.169 --> 13:46.869
I came to Horseshoe Bay
that night to see her.

13:46.913 --> 13:48.871
At least I tried, anyway.

13:48.915 --> 13:50.873
And what happened?

13:50.917 --> 13:53.223
I did everything that I could
to get here, you know?

13:53.267 --> 13:56.226
I-I hopped a school fence,
I hitchhiked, and then finally,

13:56.270 --> 13:58.663
when I-I got here,
there were police everywhere

13:58.707 --> 14:01.405
and people were saying
that Lucy had been murdered.

14:01.449 --> 14:03.886
You know? And I-I blame myself,
because I thought maybe

14:03.930 --> 14:05.888
if I could've gotten here
a little bit earlier,

14:05.932 --> 14:07.847
she might still be alive.

14:07.890 --> 14:11.067
But then I-I realized
how it would look.

14:11.111 --> 14:13.417
You know? We've been hiding
our relationship for months,

14:13.461 --> 14:16.899
and then all of a sudden, the
night that I show up, she dies?

14:16.943 --> 14:19.554
So I left before anybody
could identify me.

14:19.597 --> 14:20.947
Nancy, I...

14:20.990 --> 14:23.906
I loved Lucy.

14:23.950 --> 14:27.649
I was just, I was too afraid
to mourn her, so I buried it.

14:30.478 --> 14:34.699
Your dad must have read
your school e-mails.

14:34.743 --> 14:37.093
That's the only way he would
have known that you and Lucy

14:37.137 --> 14:39.182
were gonna meet
at your spot that night.

14:39.226 --> 14:40.444
The bluffs?

14:41.706 --> 14:43.926
The bluffs wasn't our spot.

14:45.275 --> 14:47.147
What do you mean?
What was it, then?

14:47.190 --> 14:48.539
♪ ♪

14:48.583 --> 14:51.891
♪ Ain't got time... ♪

14:51.934 --> 14:53.066
RYAN:
Wow.

14:53.109 --> 14:55.633
This place hasn't changed
in 20 years.

14:55.677 --> 14:57.418
CINDY:
Well, that's the charm of it.

14:57.461 --> 15:01.074
My dad's had me scooping since
I could reach the ice cream.

15:01.117 --> 15:02.640
So, were you working the night

15:02.684 --> 15:05.165
of the Sea Queen ceremony
in 2000?

15:05.208 --> 15:08.168
Anything to miss the
lamest event of the year.

15:08.211 --> 15:11.649
Did, uh, did-did Lucy Sable
come in that night?

15:11.693 --> 15:14.391
Sure did.
NANCY: And you didn't tell that to the cops?

15:14.435 --> 15:17.133
There's no record
of it in her file.

15:18.482 --> 15:20.963
Yeah, they didn't
take me seriously.

15:21.007 --> 15:23.531
Especially with everyone
phoning in bogus tips.

15:23.574 --> 15:24.967
But they should have.

15:25.011 --> 15:28.014
Why? What happened?

15:29.537 --> 15:30.930
Well, Lucy came in...

15:30.973 --> 15:34.107
Um, she had
this little pink backpack.

15:34.150 --> 15:37.066
She was wearing her Sea Queen
dress and sash,

15:37.110 --> 15:39.982
but she didn't look
like she'd won anything.

15:40.026 --> 15:42.028
She was so sad.

15:42.071 --> 15:46.162
Just writing in her journal,
waiting for someone.

15:46.206 --> 15:49.296
How long, how long did she wait?

15:49.339 --> 15:52.560
CINDY:
Long enough for her ice cream to melt.

15:52.603 --> 15:55.345
Eventually she left.

15:55.389 --> 15:57.565
Uh, and that's when I noticed
a town car was following her.

15:57.608 --> 16:00.655
It had this, uh,
eagle hood ornament.

16:01.699 --> 16:04.050
That's my dad's car.

16:09.577 --> 16:11.753
A couple months before
Lucy was murdered,

16:11.796 --> 16:13.755
you sent her an e-mail
from Ryan's account

16:13.798 --> 16:16.149
saying that you hoped she'd die.

16:16.192 --> 16:19.587
Oh, look, she's back.

16:19.630 --> 16:22.633
I want to know
what happened to Lucy.

16:23.983 --> 16:26.159
Why'd you do that to her?

16:30.424 --> 16:34.036
You were throwing away
your future on a nothing girl.

16:34.080 --> 16:35.211
What the hell is wrong with you?

16:35.255 --> 16:37.300
Your grades were abysmal.

16:37.344 --> 16:39.781
You slept through
how many crew practices?

16:39.824 --> 16:42.784
Okay, the night that Lucy died,

16:42.827 --> 16:46.309
you knew he was supposed to meet
her, but you got there first.

16:46.353 --> 16:49.312
I offered her a ride
so we could chat.

16:57.103 --> 17:00.019
Did you hurt her? Don't be so dramatic.

17:00.062 --> 17:05.850
I simply reminded her again
to stay away from my family.

17:05.894 --> 17:08.331
Advice I could offer you
as well.

17:10.116 --> 17:11.682
When I left,

17:11.726 --> 17:14.729
Lucy was walking up
to her house, very alive.

17:14.772 --> 17:18.733
In fact, a friend
was waiting for her.

17:18.776 --> 17:21.388
They got into an argument.

17:23.129 --> 17:25.218
What friend?

17:26.741 --> 17:28.830
It was the cop
that tried to kill you, Ryan.

17:31.398 --> 17:33.922
As far as I know, Karen Hart

17:33.965 --> 17:36.707
was the last person
to see Lucy alive.

17:45.673 --> 17:47.631
[lock buzzes]

17:47.675 --> 17:48.893
[door opens]

17:57.119 --> 17:59.252
Karen.

17:59.295 --> 18:03.343
Why were you arguing with Lucy
the night she died?

18:05.040 --> 18:06.998
Junior year, rumors spread

18:07.042 --> 18:09.784
that Lucy was sleeping
with hill-toppers.

18:09.827 --> 18:13.831
She became withdrawn, depressed.

18:13.875 --> 18:15.529
I hardly saw her.

18:15.572 --> 18:19.446
But she'd, uh, she'd always
wanted to be Sea Queen,

18:19.489 --> 18:22.275
so I nominated her
to try to cheer her up.

18:23.493 --> 18:25.713
You entered a social pariah

18:25.756 --> 18:28.585
into a popularity contest
to cheer her up?

18:30.196 --> 18:33.155
I switched out the ballot box
so that she'd win.

18:33.199 --> 18:37.116
I wanted everyone to see her
for who she was. A Sea Queen.

18:37.159 --> 18:38.900
Not a slut.

18:38.943 --> 18:40.989
But your plan
backfired because...

18:41.032 --> 18:44.253
then everybody thought that
she slept her way to victory.

18:46.995 --> 18:49.780
[sighs]
I felt awful.

18:49.824 --> 18:53.175
So I went to her house,
tried to explain myself.

18:54.220 --> 18:55.308
Hey, stop for a second.

18:55.351 --> 18:56.918
Didn't work. You've said enough.

18:56.961 --> 18:58.441
Please, please.

19:00.139 --> 19:04.926
I waited for her outside,
but by the time she came out,

19:04.969 --> 19:07.537
she made it clear
that she wanted to be alone.

19:07.581 --> 19:09.365
Let me explain.

19:09.409 --> 19:13.152
Lucy. Come on.

19:13.195 --> 19:14.588
Just leave me alone.

19:16.024 --> 19:18.374
KAREN:
And then she just rushed off.

19:18.418 --> 19:20.637
NANCY:
Did she have anything on her?

19:22.944 --> 19:24.554
She didn't.

19:26.382 --> 19:29.429
NANCY:
Okay. No-no-no journal, n-nothing?

19:32.171 --> 19:33.650
When she arrived at the house,

19:33.694 --> 19:36.262
she had her backpack
and her journal.

19:36.305 --> 19:39.613
But she had nothing
on her when she left.

19:39.656 --> 19:43.269
Her mom tore the house apart
trying to find it.

19:43.312 --> 19:46.968
What if that journal's
still in there?

19:47.011 --> 19:48.970
RYAN:
Thought they knocked this place down.

19:49.013 --> 19:51.755
NANCY:
Yeah, that's what the city
wants you to think.

19:51.799 --> 19:54.584
Found out that they changed the
house number and the street name

19:54.628 --> 19:57.152
so that it didn't become
a shrine to Dead Lucy.

19:57.196 --> 19:58.893
Couple families have lived here
over the years,

19:58.936 --> 20:00.329
but nobody has ever stayed.

20:00.373 --> 20:02.375
[bird chirping]

20:12.559 --> 20:13.516
[screeches]

20:13.560 --> 20:14.604
[screams]

20:17.433 --> 20:19.435
[panting]

20:22.003 --> 20:24.701
Yeah, I don't think
Lucy wants us here.

20:24.745 --> 20:26.486
Yeah, but why, if,
I-if her journal's inside?

20:26.529 --> 20:28.139
Yeah, I don't know.

20:28.183 --> 20:29.793
[exhales] God,
I guess the same reason

20:29.837 --> 20:31.317
she's never brought
me here before.

20:31.360 --> 20:32.927
She doesn't want me to find it.

20:34.407 --> 20:37.236
But I guess there's only
one way to find out.

20:37.279 --> 20:39.412
I have less than an hour
until I take the stand.

20:41.109 --> 20:42.937
I need to find that journal.

20:45.156 --> 20:46.636
Hey. They finish already?

20:46.680 --> 20:48.769
Yes. What is this?

20:48.812 --> 20:52.425
I got gherkins and I got clams.

20:52.468 --> 20:53.948
I'll make a salad.

20:53.991 --> 20:55.602
Yeah, but George
will probably hate it,

20:55.645 --> 20:57.908
because apparently it's
my fault that the cops are here.

20:57.952 --> 21:01.695
Right, Nick, please. For the
sake of my frazzled chakras,

21:01.738 --> 21:04.263
you and George need to
spend some time apart.

21:04.306 --> 21:06.003
Okay?

21:12.358 --> 21:13.315
Oh!

21:13.359 --> 21:15.361
What's that?

21:15.404 --> 21:17.928
Uh, just a bunch of spatulas.

21:17.972 --> 21:19.103
It's all good.

21:19.147 --> 21:20.148
BESS:
That's her skull?

21:22.019 --> 21:23.499
Everything all right, Detective?

21:23.543 --> 21:24.979
I don't know.
You tell me.

21:25.022 --> 21:27.286
GEORGE: Yeah, yeah.
Everything is great.

21:27.329 --> 21:29.375
Just me being clumsy, as usual.

21:29.418 --> 21:31.072
NICK:
Yeah, there's a reason we
call her "butterfingers."

21:31.115 --> 21:32.203
[chuckles]

21:32.247 --> 21:33.509
UNI:
Ready for the cooler, sir?

21:33.553 --> 21:35.163
Sure.

21:35.206 --> 21:37.600
So, about that cooler...

21:37.644 --> 21:39.036
No, I was just about to serve
homemade clam salad.

21:39.080 --> 21:40.081
Yeah... n-n-n-n-no.

21:45.652 --> 21:46.914
Who are you?

21:46.957 --> 21:50.047
We're the busboys.

21:50.091 --> 21:52.049
I'm the senior busboy.

21:52.093 --> 21:54.313
McGinnis was right
about you guys.

21:54.356 --> 21:56.140
You're always up to something.

21:57.968 --> 21:59.230
Search it.

22:13.419 --> 22:15.595
[sighs] I hope we can find
something in here

22:15.638 --> 22:17.727
to help exonerate my dad.

22:18.728 --> 22:20.730
[insects buzzing]

22:27.476 --> 22:29.652
Okay, let's just give
that thing some space.

22:29.696 --> 22:32.002
I'm allergic.
Yeah.

22:32.046 --> 22:34.309
Me, too.

22:43.623 --> 22:45.842
[rumbling]

22:48.758 --> 22:50.369
[rumbling stops suddenly]

22:56.723 --> 22:58.333
[shrieking]

22:58.377 --> 22:59.682
[gasps]

23:02.293 --> 23:03.643
Nancy!

23:07.516 --> 23:09.910
Nancy! Lucy, stop!

23:11.781 --> 23:13.435
What...?

23:13.479 --> 23:14.741
Okay, we got to get out of here.

23:14.784 --> 23:16.090
She doesn't want us
in this house.

23:16.133 --> 23:17.439
I am not leaving.

23:17.483 --> 23:19.398
What? What? No.
Nancy, you... Nancy!

23:26.317 --> 23:28.319
♪ ♪

23:46.816 --> 23:49.166
Lucy wrote this.

23:49.210 --> 23:51.560
I've seen her do it before.

24:13.887 --> 24:15.366
What is this?

24:15.410 --> 24:17.020
"I'm going to Dead Man's Bluff."

24:17.064 --> 24:18.239
These are different.

24:18.282 --> 24:21.460
Lucy never wanted anybody
to find these.

24:21.503 --> 24:23.462
She couldn't keep them
inside anymore.

24:30.556 --> 24:33.167
What is this?

24:58.540 --> 25:00.629
[quietly]:
Lucy's journal.

25:06.766 --> 25:08.898
Sorry about that mess
we made in the cooler.

25:08.942 --> 25:10.813
Oh, and good luck
with your inventory.

25:10.857 --> 25:12.598
Or your private party.

25:12.641 --> 25:14.991
Whichever one you decide it is.

25:16.602 --> 25:18.473
[door opens, bell jingles]

25:18.517 --> 25:19.996
[door closes]

25:23.696 --> 25:25.045
All clear.

25:25.088 --> 25:27.830
How'd you guys do it?
Where are the bones?

25:27.874 --> 25:29.353
Only place the cops didn't look.

25:29.397 --> 25:30.485
[Bess gasps]

25:30.529 --> 25:33.532
Oh. Cool.

25:36.099 --> 25:37.187
Aah!

25:37.231 --> 25:39.320
So many health code violations.

25:39.363 --> 25:40.669
This is...
Ace.

25:40.713 --> 25:42.453
ACE:
Sorry, Lucy.

25:42.497 --> 25:46.501
GEORGE:
Okay, guys, we need
to get to the courthouse.

25:52.942 --> 25:55.815
NANCY:
Entries from 1999, 2000.

25:55.858 --> 25:59.253
Hey. August 31,
day she died.

26:07.957 --> 26:10.917
I think I know why Lucy never
wanted us to find this.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.179
We got to go.

26:17.010 --> 26:19.839
BAILIFF:
The State calls Nancy
Drew to the stand.

26:22.972 --> 26:24.757
EDELSTEIN:
Ms. Drew, please take the stand

26:24.800 --> 26:26.367
to admit your journal
as evidence.

26:26.410 --> 26:29.413
I will, but not
to admit my journal.

26:29.457 --> 26:31.024
Someone else's.

26:33.809 --> 26:35.506
Lucy Sable's.

26:35.550 --> 26:37.334
[gallery murmuring]

26:40.990 --> 26:42.644
I know who killed her.

26:42.688 --> 26:45.255
And it wasn't Carson Drew.

26:53.699 --> 26:57.528
My testimony begins
in the summer of 1999...

26:59.139 --> 27:03.883
...when Lucy met a boy
who took her to a ball.

27:03.926 --> 27:05.667
And even though they
were never supposed

27:05.711 --> 27:07.843
to see each other again,

27:07.887 --> 27:12.239
this boy and Lucy fell in love.

27:14.110 --> 27:17.897
They met up again
on New Year's Eve of 1999.

27:19.681 --> 27:22.075
Then continued their secret
romance via e-mail.

27:22.118 --> 27:24.294
Lucy Sable...

27:25.687 --> 27:27.254
...and Ryan Hudson.

27:27.297 --> 27:29.473
[gallery murmuring]

27:29.517 --> 27:31.693
PROSECUTOR:
Objection.

27:31.737 --> 27:33.564
H-How is this relevant?

27:33.608 --> 27:36.045
I want to see where this goes.

27:36.089 --> 27:37.264
Overruled.

27:37.307 --> 27:39.353
Continue.

27:39.396 --> 27:44.445
NANCY:
In the spring of 2000, Ryan's
father Everett found out.

27:44.488 --> 27:47.840
And he went to Lucy directly
and told her that Ryan's future

27:47.883 --> 27:51.539
had no room
for a townie girl like her.

27:51.582 --> 27:54.585
But Lucy refused
to break up with Ryan.

27:54.629 --> 27:57.371
So Everett got what he wanted
another way.

27:57.414 --> 28:00.200
Lucy's mother lost her job.

28:00.243 --> 28:02.637
Lucy lost
her private scholarships,

28:02.681 --> 28:05.074
her chance to go to college.

28:05.118 --> 28:06.902
The Hudsons started
spreading rumors

28:06.946 --> 28:09.644
that Lucy was sleeping
with hill-toppers,

28:09.688 --> 28:11.515
and the town believed them.

28:13.169 --> 28:15.694
The slut-shaming
spread from there.

28:18.653 --> 28:21.525
Hate mail. Threats.

28:22.875 --> 28:25.965
Cruel notes passed
to Lucy in class.

28:26.008 --> 28:29.316
She kept them all.

28:29.359 --> 28:32.536
Until finally Lucy folded.

28:32.580 --> 28:34.538
She broke up with Ryan
in person,

28:34.582 --> 28:38.891
too afraid of his father
to tell him the real reason why.

28:39.935 --> 28:41.763
But by then,

28:41.807 --> 28:46.246
Lucy's life had unraveled
to the point of despair.

28:48.814 --> 28:52.513
A journal entry marked
the week before she died.

28:54.733 --> 28:57.518
"Everyone in this town hates me.

28:57.561 --> 28:59.172
Tried talking to Mom,

28:59.215 --> 29:01.609
but she just freaked out
and hid all the knives."

29:01.652 --> 29:04.351
The next entry, she wrote

29:04.394 --> 29:08.442
about a visit with her
guidance counselor Kate Drew.

29:08.485 --> 29:13.664
"Had lunch with Mrs. Drew
and her husband Carson.

29:13.708 --> 29:17.843
We ate homemade pie and used
her grandmother's silver.

29:17.886 --> 29:20.802
Everything was so nice.

29:20.846 --> 29:22.282
So beautiful."

29:23.326 --> 29:25.894
"Why can't my life
be like this?"

29:27.809 --> 29:30.594
It was at that lunch

29:30.638 --> 29:33.946
that Lucy stole one
of Kate Drew's silver knives...

29:35.948 --> 29:39.690
...and kept it in her possession
until the Sea Queen crowning.

29:39.734 --> 29:42.563
When she wrote one final entry.

29:44.739 --> 29:48.003
"I'm going up to Dead Man's
Bluff to end my life.

29:48.047 --> 29:50.789
I love you, Mom.
I hope you never find this."

29:51.877 --> 29:53.704
"I'm sorry."

29:55.706 --> 29:58.318
Her suicide note.

30:07.196 --> 30:11.331
Carson Drew did not kill
Lucy Sable.

30:11.374 --> 30:14.551
She took her own life.

30:14.595 --> 30:17.163
And for 20 years,
we told ourselves a story

30:17.206 --> 30:22.864
of a mysterious killer,
when really the killer was us.

30:22.908 --> 30:24.866
This town.

30:32.221 --> 30:36.008
But I promise to remember
the girl who lived,

30:36.051 --> 30:38.184
not the girl who died.

30:40.142 --> 30:42.797
The sole piece
of physical evidence

30:42.841 --> 30:45.974
linking Carson Drew
to the crime is a fingerprint

30:46.018 --> 30:50.457
on a knife that Lucy
took from his house.

30:53.286 --> 30:57.246
Is that enough to send a man
to trial for murder?

30:57.290 --> 30:59.640
[gallery murmuring]

31:02.948 --> 31:04.950
EDELSTEIN:
Quiet.

31:04.993 --> 31:07.430
[gavel banging]
Order.

31:26.275 --> 31:29.061
Lucy never wanted me
to figure out how she died.

31:29.104 --> 31:30.976
Yeah, I get that.

31:31.019 --> 31:35.328
Maybe she carried the trauma of
her suicide over into her death.

31:35.371 --> 31:36.764
But then why...

31:36.807 --> 31:38.592
is she haunting me?

31:38.635 --> 31:41.900
Why the bones?
What did she want me to solve?

31:43.597 --> 31:45.425
[door opens]

31:45.468 --> 31:49.298
Lucy's handwriting
has been authenticated.

31:49.342 --> 31:51.083
And there was a picture
of her with this journal

31:51.126 --> 31:52.171
in her high school yearbook.

31:52.214 --> 31:54.913
The journal is real.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.479
[exhales]

31:56.523 --> 31:58.481
EDELSTEIN:
I have considered
the new evidence

31:58.525 --> 32:01.615
and find that it is
compelling enough to hold

32:01.658 --> 32:05.706
that there is no probable
cause for Carson Drew

32:05.749 --> 32:07.795
to have killed Lucy Sable.

32:07.838 --> 32:11.451
Thus, the charges against him
are dismissed.

32:24.290 --> 32:25.552
Um, so I'm heading to The Claw.

32:25.595 --> 32:27.467
Anyway, I could bring
some stuff home.

32:27.510 --> 32:29.904
No. Uh, let's just
do it at home.

32:29.948 --> 32:31.950
Okay.

32:33.864 --> 32:37.651
I'm sorry.
For what you lost.

32:37.694 --> 32:41.655
Just be glad that you're both
finally done with my family.

32:42.699 --> 32:45.224
I'm never gonna
be free from 'em.

32:47.835 --> 32:49.054
Nancy, thank you.

32:54.581 --> 32:56.800
We missed you at The Claw today.

32:56.844 --> 32:59.281
Get used to it.

32:59.325 --> 33:02.284
I'm moving my family
up to Augusta.

33:02.328 --> 33:03.764
Took a job there.

33:03.807 --> 33:06.680
Had enough of the corruption
in the force here.

33:06.723 --> 33:09.683
Thought I'd start fresh.

33:09.726 --> 33:12.512
So that's why we're stuck
with Detective Hotshot now?

33:13.817 --> 33:17.299
Try not to break
any more federal laws.

33:17.343 --> 33:20.041
Something tells me
Detective Tamura

33:20.085 --> 33:21.912
won't be as forgiving.

33:26.482 --> 33:28.963
♪ ♪

33:32.227 --> 33:33.794
Um, I think it's best

33:33.837 --> 33:37.319
if you stick to sleeping
on my couch tonight.

33:40.757 --> 33:43.543
Oh, yeah.
Um, yeah, totally.

33:43.586 --> 33:44.718
Totally, yeah.

33:44.761 --> 33:47.286
The couch.
Yeah.

33:47.329 --> 33:50.985
Couch is, uh,
couch is a good place.

33:51.029 --> 33:53.161
Well, yeah. Just
so we can...

33:53.205 --> 33:56.034
keep being co-bosses.

33:56.077 --> 33:57.122
Co-bosses.

33:57.165 --> 33:59.254
♪ You know I'm gonna fight ♪

33:59.298 --> 34:02.562
Yeah
♪ You can bet I'm gonna fight ♪

34:03.954 --> 34:06.653
♪ Oh... ♪

34:06.696 --> 34:08.959
And friends.

34:09.003 --> 34:11.353
♪ We've only got one chance to live ♪

34:11.397 --> 34:14.139
Well...

34:14.182 --> 34:16.967
friendly co-bosses?

