35:11.370 --> 35:15.243
♪ And it all comes down to this ♪

35:16.810 --> 35:18.116
[bell jingles]

35:18.159 --> 35:20.814
Hey.
Hey.

35:22.946 --> 35:25.819
[phone rings]

35:26.341 --> 35:28.300
Hello?
So?

35:28.343 --> 35:29.997
ACE:
Just finishing what we started.

35:30.040 --> 35:30.998
NANCY:
Anything?

35:31.041 --> 35:32.913
I'm getting there.

35:39.049 --> 35:41.008
JOHN:
Okay, thank you.

35:41.051 --> 35:42.705
That was my lab calling

35:42.749 --> 35:44.794
about the hair you
messengered earlier today.

35:44.838 --> 35:46.144
Oh, do you have the results?

35:46.187 --> 35:49.886
Nancy, I think you
better sit down.

36:02.377 --> 36:03.726
You're late.

36:03.770 --> 36:07.861
I cooked your favorite
to celebrate.

36:13.301 --> 36:14.998
Nancy?

36:15.042 --> 36:17.827
I just received
a piece of evidence

36:17.871 --> 36:22.092
that proves you're still lying
about the night Lucy died.

36:28.838 --> 36:31.014
I don't... I took the stand
for you.

36:32.059 --> 36:35.062
I testified to your innocence.

36:36.629 --> 36:38.587
I followed every lead.

36:38.631 --> 36:40.676
I took every risk.

36:40.720 --> 36:42.983
Please tell me what's going on.

36:43.026 --> 36:45.246
No, you tell me.
What happened that night?

36:45.290 --> 36:47.117
And I need to hear the truth.

36:47.161 --> 36:50.077
No more lies, no more evasion.

36:50.120 --> 36:53.036
What did you do, Dad?
What did Mom do?

36:53.080 --> 36:55.691
[exhales]

36:55.735 --> 36:58.520
She was on the cliff with Lucy.

37:03.177 --> 37:06.093
Mom never hurt Lucy. How do you know that?

37:06.136 --> 37:07.660
Because I was there, too.

37:07.703 --> 37:11.185
When Lucy was still alive.

37:11.229 --> 37:13.361
What were you doing there?

37:16.059 --> 37:19.193
We were watching the fireworks.
[phone ringing]

37:19.237 --> 37:23.284
Your mom got a panicked call
from Lucy.

37:23.328 --> 37:24.503
Hello?

37:24.546 --> 37:26.461
Lucy?

37:26.505 --> 37:27.854
CARSON:
She needed help.

37:27.897 --> 37:29.029
Are you okay?

37:29.072 --> 37:30.465
Okay, just please stay
where you are,

37:30.509 --> 37:31.814
just stay put.

37:40.214 --> 37:42.260
And then we saw why.

37:44.914 --> 37:48.614
She had come to the cliff
to end her life.

37:48.657 --> 37:52.357
[baby crying]
And then the baby was born.

37:52.400 --> 37:55.229
JOHN:
Visible parturition pitting
along the dorsum

37:55.273 --> 37:56.578
of the pelvic bone.

37:56.622 --> 38:00.190
It's what happens
when a woman gives birth.

38:00.234 --> 38:04.804
This is why Lucy wanted Nancy
to find her bones.

38:08.155 --> 38:11.201
Lucy said she had kept
the pregnancy a secret.

38:11.245 --> 38:12.507
Out of fear.

38:12.551 --> 38:13.987
She'd been threatened.

38:14.030 --> 38:15.771
Everett Hudson.

38:17.251 --> 38:19.514
He spoke to her
earlier that day.

38:19.558 --> 38:22.082
CARSON:
Lucy was told
if she had the baby,

38:22.125 --> 38:25.607
her life was over,
and so was the child's.

38:25.651 --> 38:29.219
That's why she arranged

38:29.263 --> 38:31.961
to meet with Ryan that night.

38:32.005 --> 38:34.355
To, to tell him
about the pregnancy.

38:34.399 --> 38:37.140
CARSON;
We told her that we would
figure everything out.

38:37.184 --> 38:38.968
We, we just wanted to help.

38:41.014 --> 38:44.931
Lucy begged us
to take her child.

38:44.974 --> 38:46.367
And raise it.

38:46.411 --> 38:48.021
Don't let the Hudsons
know about her.

38:48.064 --> 38:50.502
CARSON:
And protect it from the Hudsons.

38:50.545 --> 38:51.894
We didn't know what to say,
we just...

38:51.938 --> 38:53.113
It's okay.

38:53.156 --> 38:54.462
...we had to calm her down...

38:54.506 --> 38:56.508
It's okay.

38:57.813 --> 38:59.772
Take care of my baby...

38:59.815 --> 39:03.558
...long enough to get help.

39:08.694 --> 39:13.089
We'd only turned away
from her for a second.

39:13.133 --> 39:17.659
When we turned back,
Lucy was... gone.

39:17.703 --> 39:20.706
I climbed down to the water
to try and find Lucy,

39:20.749 --> 39:22.316
but...

39:25.014 --> 39:27.452
I couldn't find her.

39:27.495 --> 39:31.194
Her body had already
washed out to sea.

39:33.022 --> 39:36.678
All that was left was her dress.

39:36.722 --> 39:42.205
We never knew
if she had slipped or jumped.

39:42.249 --> 39:44.643
And through the rest
of that night,

39:44.686 --> 39:47.036
we held the baby in our arms,

39:47.080 --> 39:49.299
weighing what we should do.

39:49.343 --> 39:52.607
And by the time the sun rose
the next morning,

39:52.651 --> 39:54.304
the only thing we cared about

39:54.348 --> 39:57.133
was honoring
her mother's dying wish

39:57.177 --> 39:58.221
and keeping her safe.

39:58.265 --> 40:00.223
[baby crying]

40:00.267 --> 40:02.704
And we'd fallen in love.

40:05.228 --> 40:08.362
We decided to leave
Horseshoe Bay

40:08.406 --> 40:12.279
to keep the baby's origin
a secret.

40:19.417 --> 40:21.549
Couple years later,
we came back.

40:21.593 --> 40:24.160
Things were safer by then.

40:24.204 --> 40:25.858
Everyone believed she was ours.

40:27.860 --> 40:31.429
And we decided to stay
and raise her here.

40:32.473 --> 40:35.433
All I've ever cared about

40:35.476 --> 40:39.524
is giving her a good life.

40:39.567 --> 40:42.091
One where she'd never
have to know the truth.

40:43.702 --> 40:46.008
I was her father now.

40:46.052 --> 40:49.316
I was her father.
And that's all that mattered.

40:53.842 --> 40:56.845
Lucy's baby thrived.

40:58.020 --> 41:01.241
She grew up to be whip-smart

41:01.284 --> 41:05.637
and compassionate
and kind and...

41:05.680 --> 41:08.291
endlessly curious.

41:11.860 --> 41:14.297
And she loves solving mysteries.

41:18.127 --> 41:20.086
[crying]

41:20.129 --> 41:23.524
Your DNA wasn't a match
for the female hair.

41:23.568 --> 41:26.919
It's a mother-daughter match
for Lucy Sable.

41:32.141 --> 41:34.143
She's me.

41:36.581 --> 41:38.670
The baby is me.

42:04.783 --> 42:06.741
[woman screams, bell dings]

42:06.785 --> 42:08.743
[pencil scribbling]
